What's in the box

  • Two speakers, subwoofer, remote

    • Product Description

    Creative SBS E2900 - 2.1 Powerful Bluetooth Speaker System with Subwoofer for TVs and Computers

    Spruce Up Your House

    With the Creative SBS E2900, stream wirelessly via Bluetooth, listen to your favorite FM radio channels, or play your audio of choice directly via USB or SD card playback. For wired connectivity, connect your device to the 3.5 mm AUX-in input. To top it all off, you may also easily access and change volume and playback control settings directly on the speakers, or customize the treble and bass settings with the included wireless infra remote control.

    The Creative SBS E2900 is designed to fulfill your need for an uncompromising, high-performance audio entertainment system.

    Dimensions of Subwoofer (L x W x H): 170 x 335 x 313 mm

    Dimensions of Satellite Speakers (L x W x H): 105 x 100 x 170 mm

    Notes:

    FM Radio: FM radio scanning frequency: 87.5-108 MHz (depending on regions).

    Bluetooth: Stereo Bluetooth or A2DP profile enables wireless transmission of full stereo sound to other Bluetooth devices. To determine whether your device (notebook, PC or mobile device) is equipped with A2DP-enabled Bluetooth technology, refer to your device manufacturer's documentation / website for more information.

    USB: Supports USB flash drive (up to 32 GB) to playback your MP3 audio files. For flash drives that are FATFAT32 file system compliant.

    SD Card: Supports SD cards (up to 32 GB) to playback your MP3 audio files. For SD cards that are FATFAT32 file system compliant. Does not support SDXC cards.

    Great Audio with Far-field Drivers

    Fitted with in-house tuned far-field drivers to deliver room-filling audio, and offers stunning audio performance with 60W RMS and up to 120 Peak power.

    Deep, Rumbling Bass with Subwoofer

    Hear the roar of the bass as the front-firing MDF subwoofer delivers deep, rumbling bass during your intense, action-packed stay-in movie nights.

    Various Connectivity Options

    Comes with Bluetooth 5.0 for wireless music streaming, SD Card playback, USB MP3, FM Radio, and 3.5 mm AUX-in for wired analogue connectivity.

    Convenience and Design

    Convenient Control Buttons

    Easily access music playback and volume control from the system's front-facing control buttons.

    Included Remote Control with Treble and Bass Control Settings

    For added convenience, we have included an infra remote control so you can adjust the speaker's audio settings, volume and music playback wirelessly. You may further customize the audio with the treble and bass controls on the remote control provided to suit the audio genre you're listening to, or to fit the mood you're in!

    Backlit LED

    The Creative SBS E2900 is designed with beautiful backlit LED that features passionate hues of purple, red, and blue.

    FN
    5.0 out of 5 stars Summary: AMAZING bass + volume ONLY if you are sitting close to your monitor and speakers
    Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2022
    Verified Purchase
    The media could not be loaded.
     I love bass. Im all about bass. I also love loud volume. I always need both just like the earth needs the sun and the moon - I cannot live without either. Also, I am extremely brutally honest with my reviews and if this product scked, I would have given it a 1-star, but it is actually excellent. I also like sound that is rich and clear.

    I bought this for my 13-yr old nephew who is a gamer and likes rock music. My personal speakers at home are $600 speakers.

    On to the review:

    When I first played a song via Bluetooth with this device I was immediately very disappointed with the volume. But I kept playing songs and discovered that some songs sound better than others with this product. Some songs pack a lot of bass and this product in as able to deliver what bass and it did it well. Other songs do not have bass so they sound flat and not very loud. Some songs just sound with low volume. Other songs sound loud. I tested this with lossless rock songs and some Latin songs, with EQ adjusted to rock, and they sounded amazing - but here is the catch, they sound amazing only if sitting right in front of the speakers. Yes, I could hear the music all over my two-story house and some bass, but you ONLY hear amazing bass and volume if you are sitting in front of the speakers. And yes you will feel the vibrations, the vibrations which we bass lovers love. Yes, these can deliver that. Therefore, these speakers are 100% perfect for gamers who will sit in front of their monitor with the speakers next to the monitor or behind the monitor.

    But I did not buy these speakers for music or watching movies, I bought them for gaming. Today I happened to be playing Doom 3 BFG via steamdeck on my monitor and I connected these speakers to my steam docking station with the 3.5mm Aux cable and oh my god - the sound and bass were absolutely amazing! That game is known for having amazing sound and this device was able to deliver that amazing sound the game is known for. And it was loud. And immersive. And I was immediately in-love with the product. And this is coming from someone who owns a $600 system with crazy bass and volume.

    Other comments:
    -The volume plastic dial for some reason keeps falling off and does not stay in place, right out of the box. I wish someone could tell me how to fix it. It is getting annoying because the LED light on that does not work when it falls off and it falls off almost immediately.
    -The radio antenna is trash. Only one frequency was clear and the rest unusable. Maybe I need to buy an antenna to make the radio work? But who buys this for the radio?
    -The speakers cables are really short. I was barely able to fit the speakers behind my monitor since the cables were so short.
    -The LEDs are cool but boring. I wish we could change the pattern in which the lights change.
    -The remote is nice.

    I had my little nephew take a quick video fo hopefully capture the sound of Doom with these speakers.

    Conclusion: if you are a GAMER and you will be playing your games 3 feet or less from your monitor, then you will get *excellent bass and excellent volume* from this device. If you will also play songs and watch entertainment around 3 feet from the monitor then this is also for you. But as soon as you get out of that close proximity from the speakers, you lose that amazingness and the sound is average and less bassy So only get these if you will sit close to your monitor for gaming, music, and watching videos/movies.

    5/5 stars. Super impressed. I just hope they last a decent amount of time.
